items.title: Toddler dies after being hit by train in remote NSW
items.standfirst: Officers were told the child was walking along the road when she was clipped by a train.
items.content: A one-year-old girl has died after being hit by a train in NSW's northwest.Around 7.50pm yesterday, emergency services were called to Baranbah Street in Baan Baa, near Narrabri, an hour and a half from Tamworth, following reports that a child had been hit by a freight train.Paramedics treated the one-year-old for serious injuries before she was taken to hospital.READ MORE: Woman dies in multi-motorcycle crash in Gold Coast's south She could not be saved. Officers were told the child was walking along the road when she was clipped by a train.The 22-year-old train driver was uninjured and taken to hospital for mandatory testing.A crime scene has been established as police investigate the circumstances of the crash.Narrabri Shire Council mayor Darrell Tiemens said the incident was "devastating" for the "beautiful people" of Baan Baa, the Sydney Morning Herald reports."Our hearts go out to the family of the little girl," he said."This devastating event has deeply affected our close-knit community, and our thoughts are with the young train driver, the emergency service workers and the hospital staff who responded under such heartbreaking circumstances."For these frontline workers, it's hard enough dealing with an adult fatality, but dealing with a young child when many of these people are parents themselves, is so difficult." items.title: Man tasered after allegedly throwing spear and stabbing police officer
items.standfirst: A man has been charged with attempted murder after he allegedly threw a spear at police then s tabbed a probationary officer with a sword at a home in Sydney's south-west.
items.content: A man has been charged with attempted murder after he allegedly threw a spear at police then s tabbed a probationary officer with a sword at a home in Sydney's south-west.Police were called to a home on Werombi Road in Grasmere at 5.20pm yesterday for a welfare check.Superintendent Paul Condon said police were confronted with a 20-year-old man who allegedly had a spear, a hatchet and a 50cm sword.READ MORE: One-year-old dead after being struck by train in NSW northwest Police tried to arrest the 20-year-old before he allegedly threw the spear and stabbed the 28-year-old officer in the leg with a sword.Officers tasered the 20-year-old and took him to Campbelltown Police Station. The probationary constable was given first aid and flown to Liverpool Hospital in a stable condition.This morning the 20-year-old man was charged multiple offences including with two counts of attempted murder, four counts of wounding a person with intent to resist/prevent arrest, wounding a police officer in the execution of duty as to actual bodily harm.He is due to appear before Parramatta Local Court today.
